A sensitivity analysis of each parameter was carried out to evaluate the influence of the parameters that were determined on the derived Nusselt number correlation. As the empirical range of the Karman constant was 0.43 ≥ κ ≥ 0.35, five different constants were tested. Figure 16 shows that even when the value of κ fluctuates in the entire empirical range, there is only a very small difference between the calculated Nusselt numbers. This proves that the calculation of the derived Nusselt number correlation is insensitive to κ. Thereafter, three additional constant Prt numbers were used for sensitivity analysis. Figure 17 demonstrates that the derived Nusselt number correlations vary with different Prt numbers. The predictions where Prt was 0.9 were in better agreement with experimental data, in which a fluctuation of 0.9 ± 0.1 appeared to be valid. Additionally, an error propagation analysis of the demarcation point of the flow boundary layer (ycrit+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
